olive oil
1 tub falafel bites
1 bunch baby broccoli
1 punnet cherry tomatoes
1 packet roasted almonds
½ lemon
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bunch mint
1 packet Currants

• Halve falafel. Trim baby broccoli
• Heat a frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil
• Cook falafel and baby broccoli with a generous splash of water, tossing, until golden and tender, 4-6 mins. Season to taste

• Halve cherry tomatoes. Chop almonds
• Slice lemon into wedges
• In a bowl, combine mayo and yoghurt

• Microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 mins
• In a second bowl, combine rice, spinach and currants
• Divide rice between bowls. Top with falafel, baby broccoli, tomatoes, herb yoghurt and almonds
• Tear over mint and serve with lemon wedges